Package io.microraft.executor.impl

Class DefaultRaftNodeExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.microraft.executor.impl.DefaultRaftNodeExecutor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RaftNodeExecutor, RaftNodeLifecycleAware
    public class DefaultRaftNodeExecutor
extends Object
implements RaftNodeExecutor, RaftNodeLifecycleAware
    The default implementation of RaftNodeExecutor.

    Internally uses a single-threaded ScheduledExecutorService to execute tasks submitted and scheduled by RaftNode.

    See Also:
    RaftNode, RaftNodeExecutor

      • execute

        public void execute​(@Nonnull
                    Runnable task)
        Description copied from interface: RaftNodeExecutor
        Executes the given task on the underlying platform.

        Please note that all tasks of a single Raft node must be executed in a single-threaded manner and the happens-before relationship must be maintained between given tasks of the Raft node.

        The underlying platform is free to execute the given task immediately if it fits to the defined guarantees.

        Specified by:
        execute in interface RaftNodeExecutor
        Parameters:
        task - the task to be executed.

      • submit

        public void submit​(@Nonnull
                   Runnable task)
        Description copied from interface: RaftNodeExecutor
        Submits the given task for execution.

        If the caller is already on the thread that runs the Raft node, the given task cannot be executed immediately and it must be put into the internal task queue for execution in future.

        Specified by:
        submit in interface RaftNodeExecutor
        Parameters:
        task - the task object to be executed later.

      • schedule

        public void schedule​(@Nonnull
                     Runnable task,
                     long delay,
                     @Nonnull
                     TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Description copied from interface: RaftNodeExecutor
        Schedules the task on the underlying platform to be executed after the given delay.

        Please note that even though the scheduling can be offloaded to another thread, the given task must be executed in a single-threaded manner and the happens-before relationship must be maintained between given tasks of the Raft node.

        Specified by:
        schedule in interface RaftNodeExecutor
        Parameters:
        task - the task to be executed in future
        delay - the time from now to delay execution
        timeUnit - the time unit of the delay

      • onRaftNodeTerminate

        public void onRaftNodeTerminate()
        Description copied from interface: RaftNodeLifecycleAware
        Called by RaftNode during termination.

        The component will not receive any API call after this call.

        Exceptions thrown by implementations of this method are handled and logged by RaftNode.

        Specified by:
        onRaftNodeTerminate in interface RaftNodeLifecycleAware
